In the NestJS backend, you need to create a new route for `/create-checkout-session` that returns a Stripe checkout session. You can use the `stripe` instance created earlier in `stripe.service.ts`.

Here's how to do that:

Step 1: Create a new controller in the NestJS backend

1.1. Generate a new controller using the NestJS CLI:

```
nest generate controller payment
```

Step 2: Create route `/create-checkout-session`

2.1. Open the generated `payment.controller.ts` and import the required modules:

```typescript
import { Controller, Post, Body, Res } from '@nestjs/common';
import { StripeService } from '../stripe.service';
```

2.2. Modify the `PaymentController` class to include the `/create-checkout-session` route:

```typescript
@Controller()
export class PaymentController {
  constructor(private readonly stripeService: StripeService) {}

  @Post('/create-checkout-session')
  async createCheckoutSession(
    @Body('paymentId') paymentId: string,
    @Res() res: any,
  ) {
    // Here you can fetch amount and currency based on your system
    const amount = 1000;
    const currency = 'usd';

    const session = await this.stripeService.stripe.checkout.sessions.create({
      payment_method_types: ['card'],
      line_items: [
        {
          price_data: {
            currency,
            product_data: {
              name: 'Sample Event Ticket',
            },
            unit_amount: amount,
          },
          quantity: 1,
        },
      ],
      mode: 'payment',
      success_url: 'https://example.com/success',
      cancel_url: 'https://example.com/cancel',
      metadata: {
        paymentId,
      },
    });

    res.json(session);
  }
}

```

Now the `/create-checkout-session` route will be handled by the NestJS backend. Make sure to update the frontend's code to point to the newly created route:

```javascript
const session = await fetch("http://localhost:3000/create-checkout-session", { ... });
```

Don't forget to include the `PaymentController` in the `app.module.ts` file as well:

```typescript
import { PaymentController } from './payment/payment.controller';

@Module({
  imports: [ ... ],
  controllers: [PaymentController],
  providers: [ ... ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

Now the `fetch("/create-checkout-session")` call in the frontend will hit the new backend route in your NestJS application, and securely create the Stripe checkout session.
